  <Subject Subject_ID="300047838">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300015618</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>preliminary sketches (sketches) [300015618], sketches [300015617], visual works by material or technique [300191091], visual works (works) [300191086], Visual Works (hierarchy name) [300179869], Visual and Verbal Communication (hierarchy name) [300264552], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fairly developed sketches, most often three-dimensional ones for sculpture, but may be painted or drawn. With regard to sketches for architecture, use "preliminary sketches." For rougher sculptural sketches, use "maquettes."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para bocetos bastante desarrollados, a menudo tridimensionales para esculturas, pero pueden ser pintados o dibujados. Con respecto a bocetos para arquitectura, use "boceto preliminar". Para bocetos escultóricos más aproximados, use "maqueta".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Voorbereidende, vrij ver uitgewerkte schetsen, meestal driedimensionaal voor beeldhouwwerken, maar soms ook geschilderd of getekend. Gebruik 'voorbereidende schetsen' voor soortgelijke architectonische schetsen. Gebruik 'maquettes' voor grovere schetsen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052561/Prisma Italiaans-Nederlands (1993)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>相當詳盡的速寫，大多為雕雕塑品的立體速寫，可能是描畫或或繪製而成。建築作品相關的速寫，請用「草圖」。雕像的初步速寫，請用「小模型（maquettes）」。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Recht weit ausgearbeiteter Entwurf, meist dreidimensional für Plastiken, kann aber auch gemalt oder gezeichnet sein. In Bezug auf Skizzen für Architektur siehe ["Entwurfsskizze"](300015618). Für gröbere plastische Entwürfe siehe ["Maquette (Skulptur)"](300047837).</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
